  "body": "## Motivation\r\nimmutables are currently in the global namespace. But developers may think of them more like storage variables (which can only be assigned to in the constructor), see https://github.com/vyperlang/vyper/issues/2554. So we may want to have them in the `self` namespace.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nexample:\r\n```vyper\r\nfoo: immutable(uint256)\r\ndef __init__(x: uint256):\r\n    self.foo = x\r\n\r\ndef bar() -> uint256\r\n    return self.foo\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nAll VIPs that introduce backwards incompatibilities must include a section describing these incompatibilities and their severity. The VIP must explain how the author proposes to deal with these incompatibilities.\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\nIf this VIP depends on any other VIPs being implemented, please mention them.\r\n\r\n## References\r\nAdd any references that this VIP might reference (other VIPs/issues, links to blog posts, etc.)\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
