    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "i think constants can be thought of similarly to class or module-level variables in python, whereas immutables and storage variables are analogous to instance members. so i don't think the analogy doesn't exist, but we could maybe make it more clear in the language (maybe one way is by adding some kind of `static` decorator to constant variables?)",
