    "body": "> i think constants can be thought of similarly to class or module-level variables in python, whereas immutables and storage variables are analogous to instance members. so i don't think the analogy doesn't exist, but we could maybe make it more clear in the language (maybe one way is by adding some kind of `static` decorator to constant variables?)\r\n\r\nTo quote one sentence of the [The Zen of Python](https://peps.python.org/pep-0020/#the-zen-of-python): \"Explicit is better than implicit.\" I'm not sure yet of `static` being the one, but we should be more explicit about this, yes.",
